FBIS4-27568 "dreas106_d_94004" FBIS-EAS-94-106 Daily Report 2 Jun 1994 South Korea DPRK Said `Compelled To Withdraw' From NPT DPRK Said `Compelled To Withdraw' From NPT SK0206110294 Seoul KBS-1 Radio Network in Korean 1025 GMT 2 Jun 94 SK0206110294 Seoul KBS-1 Radio Network Korean BFN [Text] Yun Ho-chin, counselor of the North Korean embassy in Vienna and chief delegate to the International Atomic Energy Agency [IAEA], said in an interview with REUTER on 2 June that the IAEA is making an unreasonable demand for inspections and, as a result, North Korea will definitely be compelled to withdraw [taltoerul kangyobatchi annulsu opta] from the Nuclear Nonproliferation Treaty [NPT]. Stressing that North Korea's intent is revealing its nuclear transparency, Counselor Yun said that he is scheduled to have a discussion with IAEA officials this afternoon to defuse the nuclear crisis.
